# Postmortem: {incident_title}
**Incident ID**: {incident_id}
**Date**: {incident_date}
**Severity**: {P0 | P1}
**Duration**: {duration} (declared {start_time_utc} — resolved {resolved_time_utc})
**IC**: {ic_name}
**On-call Engineer**: {oncall_name}
**Tech Lead**: {tech_lead_name}
**Comms Lead**: {comms_lead_name}
**Status**: {DRAFT | IN REVIEW | FINAL}

## Summary
{2–4 sentences. What happened, what the impact was, and what fixed it.
Written for a technical audience that was not on the incident.}

## Customer Impact

**Affected scope**: {endpoints, models, regions}
**Error rate**: {peak error rate and baseline}
**Latency impact**: {if applicable}
**Estimated affected requests**: {number or percentage}
**Customer-reported issues**: {number of support tickets opened}
**SLA breach**: {Yes/No — if Yes, tiers affected}
**Status page posts**: {link to status page incident}
**Customer emails sent**: {Yes/No — if Yes, count and tiers}

def postmortem_to_public_report(pm: dict) -> dict:
    BLOCKED_FIELDS = {
        "ic_name", "oncall_name", "tech_lead_name",
        "action_items",       # replaced with high-level commitments
        "5_whys",             # replaced with a confirmed root cause sentence
        "contributing_factors_internal",
    }
    PUBLIC_SECTIONS = [
        "summary",
        "timeline_external",  # pruned to customer-visible events only
        "customer_impact",
        "root_cause_confirmed",
        "what_we_are_doing",  # high-level prevention actions, no owners/dates
        "apology",
    ]
    report = {}
    for section in PUBLIC_SECTIONS:
        if section in pm and section not in BLOCKED_FIELDS:
            report[section] = pm[section]
    return report
